{
  "title": "Time",
  "description": "Time-duration value object stored internally in milliseconds. Provides unit-converted accessors (`seconds`, `minutes`, `hours`) and arithmetic helpers (Time.add, Time.subtract, Time.addTime). Constants on the class hold canonical durations: Time.zero, Time.oneSecond, Time.oneMinute, Time.oneHour, plus the TimeInterval multipliers used by the `factor` parameter. `Time.temp` is a shared scratch instance for hot paths — do not store the reference across calls.",
